quest_title: 10ml of \(\cfrac{N}{10} \)solution of a dibasic acid will completely neutralize \(\cfrac{N}{10} \)solution of a monoacidic base if its volume added is;
explanation_txt:
In any acid base reaction, number of gram equivalents consumed of acid is always equal to that of base. In the question, since both acid base solution have same normality, equal volumes of acid ad base neutralizes each other completely. The answer is 10ml.

Acidity and Basicity doesn't matter when you are working with Normality and gram equivalents.

Acidity and Basicity matters when you are working with Molarity and moles.

explanation_txt:
\(\mathrm{f}=(2 \mathrm{n}-1) \mathrm{v} / 4 \mathrm{l}\)

\(\mathrm{f}_{2}=254 \mathrm{Hz}\)
No. of beats/sec \(=(256-254)=2\)

quest_title: A bird is sitting in a large closed cage which is placed on a spring balance. It records a weight of 25 N. The bird of mass 0.5 kg flies upward in the cage with an acceleration of 2 m/s\({}^{2}\) . The spring balance will now record a weight of
explanation_txt:
\(\quad\)Wt = \(Mg\) = 25 N (Total)

\(\quad\)Mass of cage = 2.5 - 0.5 = 2 kg

\(\quad\)For bird

\(\quad\)\(\quad\)mass (\(m\)) = 0.5 kg

\(\quad\)\(\quad\)\(R\) - \(mg\) = \(ma\)

\(\quad\)\(\quad\)\(R\) = \(m\) (\(g\) + \(a\)) = 0.5 (10 + 2) = 6 N

\(\quad\)\(\therefore \)\(\quad\)Reading = wt. of cage + \(R\)

\(\quad\)\(\quad\)Reading = \(2 \times \) 10 + 6 = 26 N

explanation_txt:
The connected plates act as a single conductor. So, effectively there are two capacitors connected in parallel. The capacity of each capacitor is given by

\(C=\cfrac{\varepsilon_0 A}{d}\)

Hence, net capacitance between \(A\) and \(B\) is given by:

\(C_{A B}=C+C=\cfrac{2 \varepsilon_0 A}{d}\)

quest_title: A source of sound emits 200\(\pi\)w power which is uniformly distributed over a sphere of radius 10m. What is the loudness of sound on the surface of sphere.
explanation_txt:
\(\mathrm{P}=200 \pi \mathrm{watt}\)
\(\mathrm{r}=10 \mathrm{m}\)
\(\mathrm{I}=\cfrac{\mathrm{P}}{\mathrm{A}}=\cfrac{200 \pi}{4 \pi r^{2}}=\cfrac{200 \pi}{4 \times \pi \times 10^{2}}\)
\(1 / 1 / 2=0.5 \mathrm{w} / \mathrm{m}^{2}\)
\(\begin{aligned} \text { No. of decibel } &=10 \log \left(\cfrac{I}{I_{o}}\right) \\ &=10 \log \left(\cfrac{0.5}{10^{-12}}\right) \\ &=10\left[\log 10^{12}-\log 2\right] \\ &=10\left[12 \log _{10}^{10}-\log _{10}^{2}\right] \\ &=10[12-0.301] \\ &=116.99=117 \mathrm{dB} \end{aligned}\)
